2. OOP Concepts (Most Asked)
Encapsulation
Wrapping data and methods into a single unit.

class Student {
    private String name;

    public void setName(String n) {
        name = n;
    }

    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }
}
Interview Question
Why use private variables?

Answer: Data hiding and security.

Inheritance
class Animal {
    void eat() {
        System.out.println("Eating");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
}
Interview Question
Can Java support multiple inheritance?

Answer: No through classes, Yes through interfaces.

Polymorphism
Method Overloading
class Demo {
    int add(int a,int b){
        return a+b;
    }

    int add(int a,int b,int c){
        return a+b+c;
    }
}
Method Overriding
class Parent {
    void show() {
        System.out.println("Parent");
    }
}

class Child extends Parent {
    void show() {
        System.out.println("Child");
    }
}
Abstraction
abstract class Vehicle {
    abstract void start();
}
